title.narrative: AR PROSAP2 - Second Provincial Agricultural Development

description.narrative: To increase the productivity and sales volume of small and medium-size producers. To achieve this, the project's strategy involves technical assistance (TA), capacity-building activities, and direct investments that contribute to long-term improvements in agricultural productivity, as well as competitiveness and market access.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I. I: | Description :All subprojects subject to environmental/social screening/assessmentaccording to E/S Manual | Due Date :27-Jan-2010

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I. J: | Description :Resettlement plan must be prepared and implemented in accordance to RFfor each subproject where it is determined that resettlementwill be involved | Due Date :27-Jan-2010

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I. K: | Description :Indeigenous people development plan must be prepared and implementedin accordance to PPF for each subproject where it is determined that IP are present in the subproject area | Due Date :27-Jan-2009

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I. L: | Description :New institutional framework proposal for the PIU study to be preparedwithin one year of effectiveness; action plan prepared withinthree months thereafter and submit to Bank; implement wit | Due Date:27-Jan-2011

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I. N (a) : | Description :SAGPyA to operate and maintain at all times during projectimplementation a PIU, an IPC and a SEU within the PIU | Due Date :27-Jan-2010

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I. N (b) : | Description :SAGPyA to ensure PIU and SEU are both headed by a Coordinator withadequate professional and administartive satff acceptable to theBank | Due Date :27-Jan-2010
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I. N (c) : | Description :SAGPyA to ensure that IPC is headed by the Secretary of SAGPyA atall times during project implementation | Due Date :27-Jan-2010

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I. O: | Description :Each relevant Decentralized Entity and Participating Province toestablish one or more SIU according to the OM and headed by a Coordinator assisted by staff acceptable to the Bank | Due Date:27-Jan-2010

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I. P: | Description :Each Participating Province to establish a PLU and a FAU according tothe OM, and assisted by staff acceptable to the Bank | Due Date :27-Jan-2010
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I. Q: | Description :SAGPyA to create and maintain during each calendar year a specificbudget line entry in the relevant annual budget | Due Date :27-Jan-2011

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I. R: | Description :SAGPyA to ensure that each participating Province has mechanisms inplace to comply with the Fiscal Responsibility Law during project implementation | Due Date :27-Jan-2010
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.C: | Description :SAGPyYA to on-lend to relevant decentralized entities for implementationof National Subprojects | Due Date :27-Jan-2010
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.D: | Description :Review with Bank implementation of ANRs after the 10thOn-farm/Off-farmsubprojetc | Due Date :27-Jan-2010
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.E: | Description :SAGPyYA to on-lend to participating Provinces for implementation ofProvincial Subprojects | Due Date :27-Jan-2010
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.F, G, H: | Description :SAGPyYA to provide grants to eligible farmers for implementationof on-farm/off-farm Subprojects | Due Date :27-Jan-2010

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2. Section I.B.3: | Description :The annual audited financial statements will be furnished to the Banknot later than six months after the end of each year. | Due Date :30-Jun-2010

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2. Section I.B.2: | Description :Semiannual Interim Unaudited Financial Reports will be submitted tothe Bank not later than 45 days after the end of each calendar year | Due Date :15-Sep-2009

title.narrative: Strategic investment plans prepared and adopted in each province receiving financing from PROSAP II
Number of hectares of new productive area as a result of improved infrastructure
Increase of on-farm and off-farm investments in beneficiary producers
Improved road transportation (annual daily transit average)
Increased provincial capacity for policy development and implementation of subprojects(low/medium/high)
Annual evaluations carried out in participating provinces discussed and disseminated
Baseline studies for each subproject finalized and available at beginning of implementation
Final evaluation carried out, discussed, and disseminated
PIU Institutional Development Study carried out and discussed
Decrease in prevalence of disease in sanitary and phytosanitary interventions

baseline.value: Specific baseline values for subprojects will be determined as each subproject selected is prepared

actual.value: OIE Status of "country with negligible risk" maintained
